Multiple buckets are separated by a comma.When specifying SELECT bucket_name.* for all fields, the bucket name will not appear in the result set; while specifying SELECT * FROM bucket_name adds the bucket name to the result set.SELECT * FROM `travel-sample` WHERE type="hotel";
[ { "travel-sample": { "address": "Capstone Road, ME7 3JE", "alias": null, "checkin": null, ...SELECT `travel-sample`.* FROM `travel-sample` WHERE type="hotel";
[ { "address": "Capstone Road, ME7 3JE", "alias": null, "checkin": null, ...

The name of the field or fields, separated by a comma, to be in the query's
                  ResultSet, such
                  as:SELECT id, airline, stops FROM `travel-sample` WHERE type="route";

To use a field within an array, use [0] after the array name,
                  followed by a period and the field name, such
                  as:SELECT schedule[0].day FROM `travel-sample` WHERE type="route";
